ls `InitializeSession()` which applies `EventTurnStart` transition, so phase should be ACTIVE\\n2. **TurnID** - should be generated in `InitializeSession()`\\n3. **PendingPromptAttribution** - calculated in `InitializeSession()` via `calculatePromptAttributionAtStart()`\\n4. **LastInteractionTime** - set in `condenseAndFinalizeSession()` after condensation\\n5. **Phase transition to IDLE** - happens in `condenseAndFinalizeSession()` when calling `TransitionAndLog()`\\n\\n---\\n\\n### 5. **How Metadata is Used in UI**\\n\\nThe `explain` command (which displays checkpoint details) reads from:\\n\\n- **`store.ReadCommitted(ctx, checkpointID)`** → Returns `CheckpointSummary` with:\\n  - CheckpointID, Strategy, Branch, CheckpointsCount, FilesTouched\\n  - Sessions array with paths to metadata files\\n  - TokenUsage aggregated\\n\\n- **`store.ReadLatestSessionContent(ctx, checkpointID)`** → Returns `SessionContent` with:\\n  - `CommittedMetadata` (per-session metadata)\\n  - `Transcript` (full.jsonl bytes)\\n  - `Prompts` (prompt.txt content)\\n\\nThe UI displays:\\n- Checkpoint ID and timestamp\\n- Agent type and model name\\n- Intent (from first prompt)\\n- Outcome (from AI-generated summary, if available)\\n- Interactions (prompt/response pairs parsed from transcript)\\n- Files modified\\n- Associated git commits (via `Entire-Checkpoint` trailer search)\\n\\n---\\n\\n### 6. **\\\"Checkpoint Not Found\\\" Error**\\n\\nThis error occurs when:\\n1. **`store.ReadCommitted()` returns nil** - checkpoint metadata doesn't exist on `entire/checkpoints/v1` branch\\n   - Returned at line 79 in `manual_commit_condensation.go`\\n2. **Checkpoint ID not found in committed checkpoints** - happens in `explain.go:239` when prefix doesn't match any CheckpointInfo\\n3. **Missing metadata files** - path does not exist in the checkpoint sharded directory on metadata branch\\n\\nThe key is that metadata **must** be written to the `entire/checkpoints/v1` branch via `store.WriteCommitted()` to