ken usage (when available)\\n   - User turns/prompts count\\n   - Model name\\n   - Session duration (from timestamps)\\n4. **Creates session metadata directory** at `.entire/metadata/<session-id>/`\\n5. **Initializes session state** via `strat.InitializeSession()` \\n6. **Saves checkpoint** via `strat.SaveStep()` to the shadow branch\\n7. **Condenses session** to permanent storage on `entire/checkpoints/v1` branch\\n8. **Offers to amend** the last commit with `Entire-Checkpoint: <checkpoint-id>` trailer\\n\\n### 3. **What metadata it creates/requires**\\n\\n**Metadata created by attach:**\\n\\nSession state file (`.git/entire-sessions/<session-id>.json`):\\n- `SessionID` - unique identifier\\n- `BaseCommit` - HEAD commit hash\\n- `WorktreePath` - absolute path to worktree\\n- `WorktreeID` - git worktree identifier\\n- `StartedAt` - session start time\\n- `StepCount` - number of checkpoints (initially 0)\\n- `UntrackedFilesAtStart` - files that existed at session start\\n- `AgentType` - agent type (claude-code, gemini, etc.)\\n- `ModelName` - LLM model used\\n- `TranscriptPath` - path to transcript file\\n- `LastPrompt` - first user prompt (truncated)\\n- `CLIVersion` - CLI version that created it\\n- `TurnID` - unique ID for current agent turn\\n\\nSession metadata directory (`.entire/metadata/<session-id>/`):\\n- `full.jsonl` - Session transcript (normalized for Gemini)\\n- `prompt.txt` - First user prompt (written by attach if prompt extraction succeeds)\\n\\nShadow branch checkpoint data:\\n- Written via `WriteTemporary()` with:\\n  - Modified files list\\n  - New files list\\n  - Deleted files list\\n  - Metadata directory path\\n  - Commit message\\n\\nCommitted checkpoint data (on `entire/checkpoints/v1` branch):\\n- Root `metadata.json` (CheckpointSummary):\\n  - `checkpoint_id` - 12-hex-char identifier\\n  - `strategy` - \\\"manual-commit\\\"\\n  - `checkpoints_count` - number of checkpoints\\n  - `files_touched` - merged from all sessions\\n  - `cli_version` - CLI version\\n  - `sessions` - array of SessionFilePaths\\n\\n- Session subdirectory `<index>/metadata.json` (CommittedMetadata):\\n  - `checkpoint_id` - 12-hex-char ID\\n  - `session_id` - session identifier\\n  - `strategy` - \\\"manual-commit\\\"\\n  - `created_at` - checkpoint creation time\\n  - `checkpoints_count` - number in this session\\n  - `files_touched` - files modified/created/deleted\\n  - `agent` - agent type (populated by attach)\\n  - `model` - model name (extracted by attach if available)\\n  - `token_usage` - TokenUsage object (calculated by attach)\\n  - `session_metrics` - duration, turn count (extracted by attach)\\n  - `cli_version` - CLI version\\n\\n### 4. **How it interacts with checkpoint/session system**\\n\\nThe interaction flow:\\n\\n```\\nrunAttach()\\n  ├─ Validate session ID\\n  ├─ Read transcript from agent\\n  ├─ Extract metadata:\\n  │  ├─ First prompt (via extractFirstPromptFromTranscript)\\n  │  ├─ Modified files (via DetectFileChanges + transcript analysis)\\n  │  ├─ Token usage (via agent.CalculateTokenUsage)\\n  │  ├─ Turn count (via countUserTurns)\\n  │  ├─ Model name (via extractModelFromTranscript)\\n  │  └─ Duration (via estimateSessionDuration)\\n  ├─ Create session metadata directory\\n  ├─ Write transcript to metadata directory\\n  ├─ Write prompt.txt to metadata directory\\n  ├─ Initialize session state (creates BaseCommit, WorktreePath, etc.)\\n  ├─ Enrich session state with transcript-derived metadata\\n  ├─ Call strat.SaveStep() → writes to shadow branch via checkpoint.GitStore.WriteTemporary\\n  ├─ Call strat.CondenseSessionByID() → writes to entire/checkpoints/v1 via checkpoint.GitStore.WriteCommitted\\n  └─ Transition session phase to IDLE\\n```\\n\\n### 5. **What could cause \\\"checkpoint not found\\\" in the UI**\\n\\n**Root causes:**\\n\\n1. **Session not condensed**: The `SaveStep()` writes to shadow branch, but `CondenseSessionByID()` must run to write the final metadata to `entire/checkpoints/v1`. If condensation fails (line 212 in attach.go), the checkpoint exists on shadow branch but NOT on the metadata branch where the UI reads from.\\n\\n2. **Missing metadata.json files**: The `ReadCommitted()` function (checkpoint/committed.go:738) reads the root `metadata.json` from the `entire/checkpoints/v1` branch tree. If this file is missing or malformed, \\\"checkpoint not found\\\" is returned.\\n\\n3. **Checkpoint ID mismatch**: The CLI uses a 12-hex-char checkpoint ID. If the ID in the user commit trailer doesn't match an entry in `entire/checkpoints/v1`, lookup fails.\\n\\n4. **Session not fully created**: If `InitializeSession()` fails to set `BaseCommit` (line 48 in manual_commit_git.go), `SaveStep()` cannot create a valid shadow branch.\\n\\n5. **Missing session subdirectory**: The UI needs the `<index>/` subdirectory (with `metadata.json`, `full.jsonl`, `prompt.txt`) under the checkpoint path. If the condensation skips this, the UI cannot find the data.\\n\\n**Most likely in attach scenario:**\\n\\nLooking at line 212 in attach.go:\\n```go\\ncheckpointIDStr, condenseErr := condenseAndFinalizeSession(logCtx, strat, sessionID)\\n```\\n\\nIf `condenseErr != nil`, the UI will show \\\"checkpoint not found\\\" because:\\n- Shadow branch checkpoint was created successfully\\n- But condensation to `entire/checkpoints/v1` failed\\n- UI only reads from `entire/checkpoints/v1` (the permanent metadata branch)\\n- Shadow branch is ephemeral and not exposed to UI\\n\\nThe plan doc at `/Users/ninawork/entire/devenv/cli/docs/superpowers/plans/2026-03-12-attach-checkpoint-parity.md` shows the fix implements:\\n- Writing `prompt.txt` to metadata directory before SaveStep\\n- Calculating token usage and populating it in session state\\n- Setting turn count and model name\\n- Estimating session duration\\n\\nThese ensure the session state is fully enriched **before** condensation, so that when `WriteCommitted()` reads the session state, all fields are available for the final