essionDuration -v`\\n   597→Expected: FAIL — undefined.\\n   598→\\n   599→- [ ] **Step 3: Implement estimateSessionDuration**\\n   600→\\n   601→Ensure `\\\"bytes\\\"` is in the imports of `cmd/entire/cli/attach.go` (already imported in the file).\\n   602→\\n   603→Add to `cmd/entire/cli/attach.go`:\\n   604→\\n   605→```go\\n   606→// estimateSessionDuration estimates session duration in milliseconds from JSONL transcript timestamps.\\n   607→// The \\\"timestamp\\\" field is a top-level field in JSONL lines (alongside \\\"type\\\", \\\"uuid\\\", \\\"message\\\"),\\n   608→// NOT inside the \\\"message\\\" object. We parse raw lines since transcript.Line doesn't capture it.\\n   609→// Returns 0 if timestamps are not available (e.g., Gemini transcripts).\\n   610→func estimateSessionDuration(data []byte) int64 {\\n   611→\\ttype timestamped struct {\\n   612→\\t\\tTimestamp string `json:\\\"timestamp\\\"`\\n   613→\\t}\\n   614→\\n   615→\\tvar first, last time.Time\\n   616→\\tfor _, rawLine := range bytes.Split(data, []byte(\\\"\\\\n\\\")) {\\n   617→\\t\\tif len(rawLine) == 0 {\\n   618→\\t\\t\\tcontinue\\n   619→\\t\\t}\\n   620→\\t\\tvar ts timestamped\\n   621→\\t\\tif err := json.Unmarshal(rawLine, &ts); err != nil || ts.Timestamp == \\\"\\\" {\\n   622→\\t\\t\\tcontinue\\n   623→\\t\\t}\\n   624→\\t\\tt, err := time.Parse(time.RFC3339Nano, ts.Timestamp)\\n   625→\\t\\tif err != nil {\\n   626→\\t\\t\\tt, err = time.Parse(time.RFC3339, ts.Timestamp)\\n   627→\\t\\t\\tif err != nil {\\n   628→\\t\\t\\t\\tcontinue\\n   629→\\t\\t\\t}\\n   630→\\t\\t}\\n   631→\\t\\tif first.IsZero() {\\n   632→\\t\\t\\tfirst = t\\n   633→\\t\\t}\\n   634→\\t\\tlast = t\\n   635→\\t}\\n   636→\\n   637→\\tif first.IsZero() || last.IsZero() || !last.After(first) {\\n   638→\\t\\treturn 0\\n   639→\\t}\\n   640→\\treturn last.Sub(first).Milliseconds()\\n   641→}\\n   642→```\\n   643→\\n   644→In the session state update block of `runAttach`, add:\\n   645→\\n   646→```go\\n   